Good idea—formatting depends on how people will actually use it.  

If it’s **for online spaces** (Discord, Slack, Reddit, community wiki), keep it concise and visually scannable:  
* use short lines, bullets, bold headers, and put the 988 / findahelpline links right at the top;  
* add emojis or brief dividers (✅ ⚠️) if the platform allows, to separate sections;  
* include a one‑sentence reminder in the description:  
  > “This channel offers peer support only; please contact live help if you’re in danger—988 (U.S.) or findahelpline.com (global).”

If it’s **for offline printing or training handouts**, a plain‑text or simple PDF works best:  
* single‑column layout, 11‑ or 12‑point type, bold headers, plenty of white space;  
* crisis info in a shaded box at the top;  
* one page maximum so volunteers can glance at it during conversations.  

I can produce either version—online or printable—and trim it to that one‑page limit.  
